pros:
Great work life balance;
Not bad hourly pay given your work length (160K for 3yr+ DS mgr);
Great 401k match, HSA, health insurance, parental leave policies;
Great rotation policy (your leader expect you to change your role within 2 year);

All benefits of a well established firm;
Less bureaucracy;
Open work culture

cons:
All cons of a well established firm;
Still behind some financial corporations in adapting to latest data science tools;
Can do better in terms of pay

pros:
- good work-life balance;
- relaxed atmosphere;
- low level of stress;

cons:
- not satisfying salary in relation to market average in Warsaw;
- virtually no development perspectives;
- no career path;
- low work standards, resulting with high volume of errors and slow SLAs in most areas;
- a lot of meaningless "calls", bringing no real solutions, but burning time;

1.  Hard work pays off but not in proportion;
2. Bureaucratic and "Slothy";
3. Worth joining only when you want to go slow and steady. For highly proactive and energetic it may backfire !!

Leaders (Band 40 and above) tend to be duplicitous, cruel and only concerned about a narrow scope of interest;
Employee development is given lots of lip service and not many real results resulting in a company where advancement from the ranks is nearly impossible;
Overly complex matrix organization structure that gets in the way of real innovation;
For a Fortune 100 company they tend to be skinflints with regard to travel, expense reimbursement, etc.
